<TITLE> US official says FBI will assist </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 4 (bdnews24.com) - A US official has said the FBI will assist in the Bangladesh government's investigation into the BDR mutiny. "We have received a request from the government of Bangladesh for the FBI to help in forensic investigation into the mutiny," State Department spokesman Gordon Duguid told a press briefing in Washington on Tuesday. "And I believe the FBI has agreed to do that," he said. Prime minister Sheikh Hasina has sought forensic expertise from the US and UK in the aftermath of the Feb25-26 armed uprising by BDR border guards. US ambassador James F Moriarty told reporters on Tuesday that he had notified Washington of the request. bdn
